<section class="story-section">
  <h2 data-cms-field="ueber_nizza_h2">Nice 2026</h2>
  <p data-cms-field="ueber_nizza_p1">April 2026: Qualification in Brasília. Back in my country, for the biggest race of my life. Then Ironman World Championship Nice. The goal everything is building towards. Every hour on the bike, every kilometer in the water, every run in the dark before sunrise.</p>
  <p data-cms-field="ueber_nizza_p2">Amateur — for now.</p>
</section>

<section class="story-section">
  <h2 data-cms-field="ueber_sprachen_h2">Four Languages</h2>
  <p data-cms-field="ueber_sprachen_p1">Portuguese. English. Italian. German. Not because it looks good on a resume — because every language is a different version of me. In Portuguese I'm loud and soft. In English direct and clear. In Italian melodic. In German? I still struggle sometimes. But I like to fight.</p>
  <p class="story-inline-quote" data-cms-field="ueber_sprachen_quote1">"From mountains and lakes to techno parties and dance — that's all within my life range."</p>
</section>

